item.description:
Approach 1: Brute Force O(n^2)
Approach 2 : Two-pass Hash Table O(n) / O(n)
Approach 3 : One-pass Hash Table O(n) / O(n)
`python
def two_sum(nums: List[int], target: int) -&gt; list[int]:
table = {}
for v, i in enumerate(nums):
remain = target - v
if remain not in table.keys():
table[v] = i
else:
return [table[remain], i]
`
